Each instructions is run in basic gates like XOR, OR, AND, NAND, which are consist of CMOS circuits. CMOS - Complementary MOSFET circuits. These curcuits input 0 and/or 1 based on the power given. CMOS consists of two complemnetary transistors, NMOS, PMOS. The simpliest CMOS circuit is inverter (INV) (NOT) logic; From it NAND component can be created! Source is github os01/Operating_Systems_From_0_to_1.pdf
